    "description": {
      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.R1ew21i3luHJHfV5]{UM5 Ch.6: Gear}</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"color: #191813; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">These attachments muffle the flash and sonic blast of explosively propelled firearms. By slowing the expanding gases exiting the barrel, the suppressor stems the acoustical signature, but does not silence it completely—reducing it to merely loud instead of deafening. Suppressors cannot be used on shotguns, heavy weapons, or weapons rated higher than TL3 (most of which</span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"color: #191813; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">don’t need it in any case). Affixing a suppressor takes a standard action.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You don’t automatically reveal your location if you are hiding and make a ranged attack. Anyone within the weapon’s normal range increment is still aware that a weapon has been fired, but not necessarily from where or by whom.</span></p>",
